# Shell scripts must stay LF — the CI runners are Linux, and a Windows checkout
# that flips build-site.sh to CRLF breaks `bash build-site.sh` ("set: pipefail:
# invalid option name") and therefore the OVH deploy. eol=lf forces LF on checkout
# regardless of the local git autocrlf setting.
*.sh text eol=lf

# Normalise line endings repo-wide: store LF and check out LF everywhere, so a
# CRLF working tree (Windows / some mounts) stops showing every file as
# "modified". This project is Linux-first (CI + OVH deploy) and wants LF
# throughout. Binaries are pinned so they are never touched. After adding this,
# run once to clear any already-CRLF blobs:  git add --renormalize . && commit.
* text=auto eol=lf
*.png binary
*.ico binary
*.zip binary
